The InterAcademy Partnership (IAP) http://www.interacademies.org: &#xd;
&#xd;
IAP is the global network of science, engineering &amp; medical academies working together to provide independent expert advice on scientific, technological &amp; health issues.&#xd;
&#xd;
Under InterAcademy Partnership, more than 130 national and regional member academies work together. IAP has four regional networks (EASAC, NASAC, IANAS, AASSA). EASAC is one of the four regional networks of IAP. &#xd;
&#xd;
•	It works closely with its member academies to strengthen the role that science plays in society and to advise public officials on the scientific aspects of critical global issues&#xd;
•	It helps to create science academies in countries where academies do not exist and assists young and small academies to become more prominent in their own countries&#xd;
•	It sponsors programmes for young scientists designed to help them build strong foundations for successful careers and to more effectively engage decision makers

